Package de.engehausen.treemap

Contains the base elements needed to work with tree maps.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ICancelable
    State indicator for an operation.
    IColorProvider<N,C>
    Provides a color for a rectangle.
    IGenericTreeMapLayout<N,T extends java.lang.Number>
    Tree map layout interface for different kinds of weighted tree models.
    IGenericWeightedTreeModel<N,T extends java.lang.Number>
    An extension to the weighted tree model which supports arbitrary number-based weight types.
    IIteratorSize<E>
    An iterator that indicates the number of items it will expose.
    ILabelProvider<N>
    Provides a label for a rectangle.
    IRectangle<N>
    Represents the rectangle in a tree map.
    IRectangleRenderer<N,G,C>
    Renderer for rectangles.
    ISelectionChangeListener<N>
    Listener that is to be notified when the selection changes in the tree map.
    ITreeMapLayout<N>
    Tree map layout interface.
    ITreeModel<N>
    A tree model.
    IWeightedTreeModel<N>
    A tree model which provides a "weight" for each of its node.
    NumberArithmetic<T extends java.lang.Number>
    Generic number arithmetic for IGenericWeightedTreeModel instances.

Package de.engehausen.treemap Description

Contains the base elements needed to work with tree maps. Samples how everything is being used in action can be found in the examples package.
